EstClass: Type-3: High effort (5 or more surveys)

EstClass: Type-3: High effort (5 or more surveys)
Comments: HO: AUC mainstem estimate (N=3092) based on a 75% OE and 23 d SL, five surveys conducted from Oct 17 and Nov 14, artificial zeros Oct 10, Dec 14 ; spawning channel estimate (N=97) based on a 75% OE and 12 d survey life. SL: Maximum Likelihood AUC estimate: 2831 +/- 25%.

EstClass: Type-3: High effort (5 or more surveys)
Comments: Mainstem AUC based on a 23 d SL and 75% OE, survey dates Oct 22 to Dec 10, artificial zeros Oct 15 and Dec 31; Spawning channel based on a 75% OE and 12 d SL.   Survey on Nov 6 could not be conducted due to high water.  Unique default expansion factor of 3.0.  Estimate includes Spawning channel AUC of 276 + River AUC of 4858. Note: Two female coho opportunistically observed in Nahatlatch in Jan.  NuSEDs estimate needs to be changed to include spawning channel fish.

EstClass: Type-3: High effort (5 or more surveys)
Comments: Nahatlatch estimate includes the Spawning Channel AUC and the mainstem AUC.  Mainstem survey dates Oct 15 to Nov 25, artificial zeros Oct 1 to Dec 31, peak count on the last survey. Mainstem AUC based on a 75% OE and 23 d SL; Spawning channel AUC based on a 75% OE and 12 d SL.

EstClass: Type-3: High effort (5 or more surveys)
DataQualClass: 8  Moderate effort (2-4 surveys), seasoned crew, standardized method, captured peak spawning period
Comments: AUC estimate based on a 75% OE and 23 d SL.  An adjusted aerial survey was included in the AUC calculation.  The Dec 3 spawner count from aerial survey was adjusted downward by 79% based on the concurrent float and aerial surveys counts conducted on Dec 17th.  No Coho were observed in the spawning channel in 2014.  Four surveys were conducted btw Nov 3 and Dec 17.  Hydrological conditions were similar to spring freshet. Concern that flows may have been scouring to fresh redds.

EstClass: Type-3: High effort (5 or more surveys)
DataQualClass: 6  High effort (?5 surveys), seasoned crew, standardized methods, captured spawning period, favourable environmental conditions during spawning period
Comments: AUC estimate (N=347) based on a 75% OE and 23 d SL.  Seven surveys were conducted btw Oct 30 and Dec 16.  Zero counts added to start and end dates.  Expanded peak count estimate (N=5) for the spawning channel was based on a 2.5 small system expansion factor and added to the AUC estimate.

EstClass: Type-3: High effort (5 or more surveys)
DataQualClass: 6  High effort (?5 surveys), seasoned crew, standardized methods, captured spawning period, favourable environmental conditions during spawning period
Comments: Float and aerial survey methods used.  AUC estimate based on a 75% OE and 23 d SL.  Nine surveys were conducted btw Oct 19 and Dec 12; the last two surveys were aerial surveys.  Zero count start and end dates were added.  The Nov 8 survey was removed from the calculation as a result of high flows and poor counting conditions.  An adjustment was made to the aerial surveys spawner counts as per the 2014 Nahatlatch adjustment.  Two surveys were conducted on the spawning channel but no fish were observed; the channel had silted over.

EstClass: Type-3: High effort (5 or more surveys)
DataQualClass: 6  High effort (?5 surveys), seasoned crew, standardized methods, captured spawning period, favourable environmental conditions during spawning period
Comments: AUC estimate based on a 75% OE and 23 d SL.  Six surveys were conducted btw Oct 23 and Dec 18.  Zero count start and end dates were added.  Two surveys were not conducted: Nov 6  due to ice; Nov 13 due to heavy rain and wind.  No surveys were conducted on the spawning channel in 2017.  No aerial survey was conducted on Nahatlatch in 2017.

EstClass: Type-3: High effort (5 or more surveys)
DataQualClass: 6  High effort (?5 surveys), seasoned crew, standardized methods, captured spawning period, favourable environmental conditions during spawning period
Comments: Combined Estimate. AUC estimate based on a 75% OE and 23 d SL.  Ten surveys were conducted btw Oct 22 and Jan 11.  Zero count start and end dates were added.  The Nov 6 survey was removed from the calculation due to poor counting conditions as a result of high water.  An Expanded peak count estimate was also calculated for the Spawning channel based on a 2.94 small system expansion factor.  Only a single survey was conducted on the Spawning channel on Nov 6. Total Estimate=AUC estimate (N=4874) + Expanded PCEst (N=41). The regular survey period was extended in this year due to milder temperatures. Coho were counted into January.

EstClass: Type-3: High effort (5 or more surveys)
DataQualClass: 6  High effort (?5 surveys), seasoned crew, standardized methods, captured spawning period, favourable environmental conditions during spawning period
Comments: AUC estimate based on a 75% OE and 23 d SL.  Eight surveys were conducted btw Oct 22 and Jan 11.  Zero count start and end dates were added.

EstClass: Type-3: High effort (5 or more surveys)
DataQualClass: 6  High effort (?5 surveys), seasoned crew, standardized methods, captured spawning period, favourable environmental conditions during spawning period
Comments: Combined estimate. AUC estimate (N=5223) for the mainstem based on a 75% OE and 23 d SL.  Eleven surveys were conducted btw Oct 13 and Dec 21.  Zero count start and end dates were added. Two surveys were removed from the calculation: The Oct 13 survey due to low Stream Visibility and poor environmental conditions; and Nov 9 survey due to poor Water Clarity and environmental conditions. AUC estimate (N=88) for the Spawning Channel based on a 75% OE and 9 d SL. Five surveys were conducted btw Nov 9 and Dec 7. A zero count start date was added. No surveys were removed from the calculation. The total escapement estimate (N=5311) includes the mainstem AUC estimate plus the Spawning Channel AUC estimate.

EstClass: Type-3: High effort (5 or more surveys)
DataQualClass: 6  High effort (?5 surveys), seasoned crew, standardized methods, captured spawning period, favourable environmental conditions during spawning period
Comments: Combined estimate. An AUC estimate (N=2099) for the mainstem based on a 75% OE and 23 d SL.  Five surveys were conducted btw Oct 11 and Dec 9.  A zero count start and end date were added. No surveys were removed from the calculation. Surveys scheduled for Nov 15, 22 or 29 were not conducted due to high water. An AUC estimate (N=273) for the Spawning Channel based on a 75% OE and 9 d SL. Three surveys were conducted btw Oct 25 and Nov 8. A zero count start and end date were added. No surveys were removed from the calculation. No surveys of the Spawning Channel were conducted after Nov 8 due to high water. The total escapement estimate (N=2372) includes the mainstem AUC estimate plus the Spawning Channel AUC estimate.

EstClass: Type-1: Fence or Fishway with virtually no bypass
DataQualClass: 1  True Abundance with virtually no bypass
Comments: Bonaparte fishway was operational from Sep 1 to Nov 29.  Peak migration occured btw Sep 23 and Sep 29 (n=254); smaller pulse occurred btw Oct 21 and Oct 25 (n=95).  The first fish was recorded on Sep 15 and the last fish on Nov 14.  No harvest or brood reported on the spreadsheet.

EstClass: Type-1: Fence or Fishway with virtually no bypass
DataQualClass: 1  True Abundance with virtually no bypass
Comments: Fishway was not operational in 2018 due to breach in fishway walls and an inability to fix it due to unseasonally high water. Severe forest burns in the upper watershed have contributed to high water as trees and organics no long retain or evapotranspire water. Overland and we assume aquifer flows are uninhibited by normal water retention and removal processes in the Bonaparte watershed.  An attempt was made by the Bonaparte Band to run a collection fence for capturing and moving fish above the fishway but it failed due to high water. One Coho adult was moved above the fishway.

EstClass: Type-1: Fence or Fishway with virtually no bypass
DataQualClass: 1  True Abundance with virtually no bypass
Comments: First fish observed through the fishway on Sep 24 and last fish observed on Nov 6.  The fishway operated between Sep 24 and Dec 5.

EstClass: Type-1B: Fence with significant Breach
DataQualClass: 3  Breach(s) reported or fence in later or removed early; no adjustment to estimate made.
Comments: Bonaparte fishway operated from Sep 15 to Nov 25 by the SFC. Two outages occurred during the operational period. The first occurred between Oct 2 and Oct 9; no counter or graphics data were recorded during this time. The second resulted in the loss of graphics data btw Nov 3 and Nov 16; however, raw counter records were still recorded. A peak count of 376 net up fish was recorded on Nov 8. No video calibration was done in 2020 due to theft of the equipment early in the season. As a result, Instream applied 2019 up count video accuracies to the daily counts by channel in 2020. Instream's estimate for Bonaparte Coho was reported for 2020.

EstClass: Type-1: Fence or Fishway with virtually no bypass
DataQualClass: 1  True Abundance with virtually no bypass
Comments: The Bonaparte fishway operated from Sep 15 to Nov 15 by the SFC. No equipment or power issues were reported in 2021. The first fish was counted on Sep 22. There was a small pulse of fish btw Sep 22 and Sep 30. No fish were reported btw Oct 1 and Oct 14. A second, larger pulse occurred btw Oct 15 and Oct 24; no other counts were reported after Oct 24. NOTE: The Bonaparte fishway was not operational in 2018.

EstClass: Type-1: Fence or Fishway with virtually no bypass
DataQualClass: 1  True Abundance with virtually no bypass
Comments: 102 fish taken for brood (99 unmarked and 3 ad/CWT'd). Estimate is a whole system count using DIDSON installed by and operated in Merritt from Oct 9 to Nov 19 by the Nicola Tribal Association. Very early freshet and very low flows during late spring and summer. May affect smolt migrations.

EstClass: Type-1: Fence or Fishway with virtually no bypass
DataQualClass: 1  True Abundance with virtually no bypass
Comments: NTA ran the DIDSON in the Coldwater.  DIDSON was installed and counting from Oct 9 to Nov 27 (was removed from Nov 13 to Nov 23 due to ice build up).  Run looked fairly normally distributed as NTA began seeing one or two fish immediately on the 9th of October with a peak on Oct 20th and tailed out to one or two fish by Nov 11th. May have been another push, can't say for sure as DIDSON was out of the water. Image quality of files was good to moderate with shadows/grainy appearance. Very early freshet and very low flows during late spring and summer. May affect fry survival.

DataQualClass: Infill

EstClass: Type-1C: Fence with significant breach
DataQualClass: 3  Breach(s) reported or fence in later or removed early; no adjustment to estimate made.
Comments: Combined estimate.  A fence was installed by NTA on Sep 12 (fish tight) and removed on Nov 23.  Two high water events were noted:  Oct 19-20 and Nov 23.  High water was anticipated in both cases.  The fence was lowered and a DIDSON was installed and operational from Oct 17 to Nov 23.  No power outages were reported during sonar operations.  Brood taken at fence: 5 M ; 3 F.  AFC Live Sampled Coho at fence: 22 M ; 34 F.  Details were provided by Jess Urquhart (NTA). Concern over the quality of the SONAR image. Estimate seems low relative to returns elsewhere and estimate of survival is very low and ER is very high based on tag expansion from esc. estimate.

EstClass: Type-1: Fence or Fishway with virtually no bypass
DataQualClass: 1  True Abundance with virtually no bypass
Comments: Combined Estimate. A fence was installed on Sep 11 by NTA. A DIDSON sonar operated briefly on Oct 3 and was pulled on Oct 4 due to a malfunction. The fence was lowered on Nov 2 due to a high water event and raised on Nov 4. Fish were counted through visually during this period. The sonar was reinstalled on Nov 6. Ice build up on Nov 18-21 and panels were lowered. Program ended on Nov 21. The fence was lowered and oberver counts were also conducted on Oct 24-26 and Oct 28-29.   This was a very successful program this year as the fence was maintained throughout the program. 182 ad clip Coho were removed at the fence for PIN status. 67 fish were removed at the fence for brood and 121 were removed upstream by SEP for brood and removed from the spawner total derived from the fence (4404-121=4283).

The fence was lowered and a DIDSON was installed and operational from Oct 12 to Nov 19. The following removals were not included in the estimate:  Brood taken: 87 M ; 106 F.  Harvest: 31 M ; 31 F.  Details were provided by Jess Urquhart (STC).

EstClass: Type-1: Fence or Fishway with virtually no bypass
DataQualClass: 1  True Abundance with virtually no bypass
Comments: The Coldwater fence was installed on Sep 9 and operated by STC. The fence, trap box and sonar were lost downstream on Nov 14 due to a major flood event. An ARIS sonar unit was operational on Sep 26 but mostly ran as backup to the fence until mid-Oct. The Final estimate (N=11473) includes the sonar count of 10,920, plus the 386 fish sampled and passed u/s through the trap, plus the 375 visual count. The estimate does not include: DOA= 1 or the 208 removed for brood:  M=103 ; F=105. Of the brood removed 55 were taken at the fence and 153 were captured by SEP. The estimate also does not include 221 CWT sacrifices at the fence.

EstClass: Type-1C: Fence with significant breach
DataQualClass: 3  Breach(s) reported or fence in later or removed early; no adjustment to estimate made.
Comments: Adjustment may be needed.  Deadman counter was not operational in 2017 due to equipment damage from summer fires.  Skeetchestn ran the brood collection fence nearly the full season according to an email from Aaron Gillespie (SFC).  It was noted that 80 Coho were counted u/s of the fence prior to it being fish tight on Sep 28.  The fence was pulled on Nov 3 due to ice and panels were put back in on Nov 8.  Fish (n=80) observed holding below the fence before it was pulled.  Peak migration occurred btw Oct 17 and 21 (n=355); smaller pulse occurred btw Nov 13 and 15 (n=83).  The fence was taken out for the season on Nov 20 and 44 Coho were observed holding below.  Brood Taken: 46 M ; 56 F.  Harvest: 27 M ; 26 F.  Escapement Sex Ratio:  M=43% ; F=57%.

EstClass: Type-1: Fence or Fishway with virtually no bypass
DataQualClass: 1  True Abundance with virtually no bypass
Comments: A resistivity counter operated from Sep 1 until its removal on Dec 12. Two distinct migration periods were observed: Sep 27-28 and Oct 8-9 - 54% of fish passage occurred over the 2-2day periods (n=350 of 640 fish). The first fish was observed on Sep 15 and the last fish on Nov 26.

EstClass: Type-1: Fence or Fishway with virtually no bypass
DataQualClass: 1  True Abundance with virtually no bypass
Comments: A resistivity counter operated from Sep 1 until its removal on Dec 15. A distinct migration period was observed: Oct 16 - 19 - 50% of fish passage occurred over the 4 day period (n=885 of 1716 fish). The first fish was observed on Sep 15 and the last fish on Nov 19.

EstClass: Type-1: Fence or Fishway with virtually no bypass
DataQualClass: 3  Breach(s) reported or fence in later or removed early; no adjustment to estimate made.
Comments: Deadman resistivity counter was operational from Sep 1 to Nov 25 and video data were recorded from Sep 1 to Nov 4. There were several periods of missing data: 1. Video validation data were not available from Sep 3 to Sep 11 or from Oct 11 to Oct 16, 2. Graphics data were not collected from Sep 11 to Sep 16., 3. Complete counter outage occurred from Sep 16 to Sep 18.  These outages resulted in limited data available btw Sep 3 and Sep 11 and no usable counter data btw Sep 11 and Sep 18.  The Coho escapement estimate from Sep 16 to Nov 25 was 2399. Confidence in these estimates is moderate due to missing data throughout Sep and a shadow and periphyton buildup on Channel 2 resulting in challenging validation conditions.  Estimate was provided by Instream.  No brood or harvest was reported by SFC.

EstClass: Type-1: Fence or Fishway with virtually no bypass
DataQualClass: 1  True Abundance with virtually no bypass
Comments: The Deadman resistivity (crump-weir) was operational from Sep 16 to Nov 30 and maintained by SFC. Video data were recorded and used to validate the counter. Due to extremely low water levels through the operational period only counter 2 channel was wetted and operational for most of the run. Counter data were randomly validated using video data from Sep 16-Oct 4 with additional validation completed on Oct 17. A total of 57 hrs of video was viewed (3% of total video available). Graphics data were inconsistenly recorded due to technical problems; the time period of the missing data was not provided, however, most of the missing graphics data occurred on Oct 17 the peak day of migration. Info obtained from Instream Report. The estimate does not inlcude brood taken from the fence site, 25 Males, 26 Females. 51 total brood.

Comments: Likely an underestimate.  The sonar was installed on Sep 22 and removed on Nov 3 as a result of ice.  Fish began to move in numbers (n=45) on Oct 11 and peak migration (n=869) occurred btw Oct 17 and Oct 19.  A storm came through on the Oct 17/18 which dropped 25.4 mm of rain in Merritt; in Hope, 49.8 mm (Oct 17) and 35.1 mm (Oct 19). EstClass: Type-1: Fence or Fishway with virtually no bypass
DataQualClass: 1  True Abundance with virtually no bypass
Comments: A DIDSON sonar unit was installed and operational from Sep 10 - Nov 13. The sonar was removed on Nov 13 in anticipation of a high water event which marked the end of the program. Due to Pink presence, infilling was conducted up until Oct 4 using historical Spius Coho daily migration proportions; and for the period of Oct 10 - Oct 15 during sonar malfunctions. The sonar estimate from Oct 5 to the end of program was 3800 and infilling from install to Oct 4 resulted in 2947 Coho. The total escapement estimate (N=6747) includes the sonar estimate (N=3800) plus the infill estimate (N=2947).

EstClass: Type-7: Infill
DataQualClass: 1  True Abundance with virtually no bypass
Comments: High flow releases from Terzaghi Dam were used to manage the excess water stored in Carpenter Reservoir, resulting in a hydrograph that ramped up on May 23, 2017, peaked at 127 m3 s-1 from June 10 to June 27, and ramped down to 5.1 cms by August 17. Terzaghi Dam discharges returned to the target WUP hydrograph prior to the historic run timing of Chinook and Coho salmon (August to December). Steelhead spawn from April to early June and the high flows may have affected Steelhead spawning (BRGMON-03 Year 6 report by Instream). Data from Intream SONAR was lost and the AUC estimate is for a different area then the SONAR counts therefore the count is not comparable between years and I have stuck with the infill.  The BC Hydro enumeration work is set to last for 10 years total at which time there will be a time series reajustment based on a better understanding of OE and SL and will include counts from Terzaghi to the Yalokom.

Comments: Dunn Cr Hatchery staff installed the fence (fish tight) on Sep 24 and removed it on Dec 3. No breaches were reported in 2021. The total count through the fence was 6005 before the following removals: Brood: 40 M; 47 F (of which, 12 M; 12 F were used for the Classroom program); Recaps: 168 M; 122 F; Fence Mortalities: 1 M; 1 F; Harvest: 43 M; 0 F. The first fish passed through the fence on Sep 24 and there were no fish recorded at the fence from Dec 1 to removal on Dec 3. Escapement Sex Ratio: M 53% ; F 47%.

EstClass: Type-2: Mark-recapture
Comments: Total Return to River was 5889 coho.  The Total Return includes the MR estimate of 5538; 282 coho below the fence (spawner only AUC) ; 28 Males and 28 Females removed for brood; 5 Male and 3 Females harvested by Splatsin' and the 2 Males and 3 Females trap morts. Exclusion fence was operating above Griffin Lake below the confluence of the Eagle and Butterball Creek - fence was breached. Large flooding event in Sicamous area on June 22, 2012 may have stranded fry returning in 2014.

EstClass: Type-1: Fence or Fishway with virtually no bypass
DataQualClass: 1  True Abundance with virtually no bypass
Comments: Spawners only used for AUC below the Eagle fence. Crazy estimate also included in Eagle R estimate. Fish came in late and a large percentage (50-60%) of the early run had a flesh eating infection of some kind on their heads and the leading edges of their dorsally placed fins. There was significant flooding in the spring of 2012 that may have impacted smolts from this brood. DIDSON used for the first time at the fence site as cold snap left several fish holding below the fence which would not move through - had to open the fence and use DIDSON count to enable fish passage to prefered spawning grounds.

EstClass: Type-1B: Fence with significant Breach + infill
DataQualClass: 2  Breach(s) reported or fence in late or removed early; adjustment to estimate made.
Comments: Estimate is the number of fish past the fence by Nov 6th expanded by average percentage past fence in previous years.  No brood removals this year as fence was topped and no fish were available in the trap.  Fish were taken from Salmon River instead. South Pass (0), Crazy (0) and the float below the Eagle fence (13- PLExp) are included in the estimate. Wild returns may have been impacted by a potential fry mortality event due to record high water and flooding in the Sicamous area during June 2012.

EstClass: Type-1: Fence or Fishway with virtually no bypass
DataQualClass: 1  True Abundance with virtually no bypass
Comments: Combined estimate.  Eagle R fence operated from Sep 29 to Dec 3.   A breach was noted on Oct 13 (human caused).  DIDSON sonar operated at the fence site from Oct 30 to Nov 3 during high water and again from Nov 18 until the program end on Dec 3.  The escapement estimate includes the fence count (N=352), the downstream expanded estimate (N=5) using a 2.5 expansion factor and the DIDSON count (N=1300).  Peak count estimate below the fence was based on spawners only.  Otters troubles were noted in the trap box and at the fence from Oct 19-26; the back of the trap box was left open to let fish escape.  The trap box was closed on Oct 27.  Spius Hatchery removed brood on Nov 10 (11 AP M ; 1 AFC M ; 8 AP F) and Nov 16, 17 (Totals: 25 AP M ; 8 AFC M ; 31 AP F ; 6 AFC F).

EstClass: Type-1: Fence or Fishway with virtually no bypass
DataQualClass: 1  True Abundance with virtually no bypass
Comments: Combined Estimate.  A fence operated from Sep 19 to Oct 12 - 101 Coho passed through.  A DIDSON operated from Oct 13 to Nov 30 and recorded 4857 Coho.  The total escapement (N=4958) includes the fence estimate (N=101) plus the DIDSON estimate (N=4857). Very high water prevented the operation of the fence and crews were unable to access the Eagle for recovery and AUC counts for long periods of time. Brood was collected above the fence by angling and seining into a stop net above enchanted forest.

EstClass: Type-1: Fence or Fishway with virtually no bypass
DataQualClass: 1  True Abundance with virtually no bypass
Comments: Combined estimate.  A fence was installed by DFO on Sep 29 and was fish tight on Oct 2.  It was removed on Nov 29.  No breaches were reported.  An ARIS sonar operated with the fence from Nov 14 to Nov 20.  Seven float surveys were conducted below the fence btw Nov 8 and Dec 12.  The total escapement estimate includes the 104 Coho that passed through the fence, the 592 Coho counted in the sonar files and the Spawners Only AUC estimate (N=51) calculated from the floats surveys conducted below the fence based on a 75% OE and 9 d SL.  The escapement estimate does not include the following removals:  Brood: 39 M ; 39 F ; Harvest:  4 M ; 3 F ; Trap Mortalities: 2 M ; 0 F.     CORRECTION: In February 2020 corrected estimate. 2017 included reaches 7, 9 and 10 in AUC was corrected to only inlclude reach 10. NEW ESTIMATE - The total escapement estimate includes the 104 Coho that passed through the fence, the 592 Coho counted in the sonar files and the Spawners Only AUC estimate (N=16) calculated from the floats surveys conducted below the fence based on a 75% OE and 9 d SL.

EstClass: Type-1B: Fence with significant Breach + infill
DataQualClass: 2  Breach(s) reported or fence in late or removed early; adjustment to estimate made.
Comments: Combined estimate.  A fence was installed and fish tight on Oct 4. Due to large numbers of returning Sockeye, fish were counted through an opening in the trap box where they passed in single file. Fence panels were dropped on Nov 2 due to high water. An ARIS sonar operated with the fence from Nov 1 to Nov 28. The sonar went down on numerous occasions btw Nov 1 and Nov 7.  Fence was removed on Nov 28.  The total escapement estimate includes the Coho that passed through the fence and the Coho counted in the sonar files. The escapement estimate does not include the following removals:  Brood: 35 M ; 36 F ; CWT sampling:  93 M ; 40 F ; Trap Mortalities: 0 M ; 5 F.

EstClass: Type-1: Fence or Fishway with virtually no bypass
DataQualClass: 7  High effort (?5 surveys), new or untrained crew, variable methods, partial capture of spawning period, unfavourable environmental conditions during spawning period.
Comments: Combined estimate.  A fence was installed and fish tight by DFO on Oct 3.  It was removed on Dec 2.  No breaches were reported.  A DIDSON sonar operated with the fence from Nov 5 to Nov 29.  Three float surveys were conducted below the fence btw Nov 12 and Nov 26.  The total escapement estimate includes the 480 Coho that passed through the fence, the 3211 Coho counted in the sonar files and the Expanded peak count estimate (N=3) calculated from the floats surveys conducted below the fence based on a 2.5 large system expansion factor. The escapement estimate does not include the following removals:  Brood: 33 M ; 33 F ; AFC Harvest:  64 M ; 54 F ; Trap Mortalities: 0 M ; 1 F.

EstClass: Type-1: Fence or Fishway with virtually no bypass
DataQualClass: 1  True Abundance with virtually no bypass
Comments: Combined estimate.  A fence was installed by DFO on Oct 1 and was removed on Dec 2.  No breaches were reported.  An DIDSON sonar was installed on Oct 27 and operational until its removal on Nov 27; the sonar did not operated from Nov 12-26 when the fence was closed; the sonar did, however, run on Nov 18.  Two float surveys were conducted below the fence on Nov 10 and Nov 17.  The total return to the fence (N=5706)  includes the 541 (M=290; F=251) Coho that passed through the fence and the 5165 Coho counted in the sonar files. The total return to the fence does not include the following removals:  Brood: 35 M ; 34 F ; Harvest:  65 M ; 34 F ; Trap Mortalities: 0 M ; 0 F. The total return to spawn (N=5565) includes: 380 (M=201 ; F=179) Coho released upstream, 5165 sonar count and the Expanded spawner count (N=28) based on a 2.5 expansion factor for large systems calculated from the Nov 17 float survey conducted below the fence. South Pass fish (N=8) were removed from the total return to spawn.  Sex ratio from the fence: M=54% ; F=46%.

EstClass: Type-1B: Fence with significant Breach
DataQualClass: 3  Breach(s) reported or fence in later or removed early; no adjustment to estimate made.
Comments: Combined estimate.  A fence was installed by DFO on Sep 28 and was removed on Dec 9.  There was a significan breach in the fence from Nov 15-19 when the fence was blown out and the sonar was not operational.  The sonar was up and running again on Nov 20. No sonar files were counted after Dec 3 due to the bad quality of the image. Three float surveys were conducted below the fence on Nov 9, 23 and Dec 7; no spawners were observed.  The total return to the fence (N=7150)  includes the 1386 (M=788; F=330; UNK=268) Coho that passed through the fence and the 5764 Coho counted in the sonar files. The total return to the fence does not include the following removals:  Brood: 39 M ; 41 F ; Harvest:  70 M ; 29 F ; Trap Mortalities: 0 M ; 0 F. The total return to spawn (N=6938) includes: 1207 (M=679 ; F=260; Unk=268) Coho released upstream plus the sonar count (N=5764) minus South Pass Cr (N=30) and Crazy Cr N=3) fish. No spawning fish were observed in Seg 10 (below the fence). Return to Spawn Sex Ratio: M=72% ; F=28%.

EstClass: Type-1: Fence or Fishway with virtually no bypass
DataQualClass: 1  True Abundance with virtually no bypass
Comments: Combined estimate.  Unsure when the fence was operational but it was removed on Dec 2, 2015.  No breaches were reported.  Spius Hatchery removed 39 M and 28 F for brood.  Doug Allen reported fence count & brood removal info via email on Jan 14, 2016.  Sex Ratio for the Salmon R in 2015:  M = 71% ; F = 29%.  Streamwalks were conducted below the fence by the LSIB.  The AUC Spawners Only estimate (N=11) below the fence was included in Salmon R fence estimate.  AUC estimate was based on a 75% OE and 9 d SL.  Seven surveys were conducted btw Oct 16 and Nov 26.  Zero count was added to the end date.

EstClass: Type-1: Fence or Fishway with virtually no bypass
DataQualClass: 1  True Abundance with virtually no bypass
Comments: Combined estimate.  A fence was operational from Sep 7 to Nov 22, 2016.  No breaches were reported.  No brood was removed.  Fish were not sexed through the fence.  Multiple survey methods were utilized downstream of the fence in 2016:  Streamwalks and floats conducted by the LSIB.  An expanded peak count estimate for fish below the fence was based on a 2.87 small system expansion factor.  Six surveys were conducted btw Oct 14 and Nov 25.  Total escapement (N=1363) = Fence estimate (N=1340) plus the PCExp estimate (N=23).

EstClass: Type-1: Fence or Fishway with virtually no bypass
DataQualClass: 1  True Abundance with virtually no bypass
Comments: Combined estimate.  An expanded peak count estimate (N=21) was calculated for surveys conducted below the fence based on a 3.04 small system expansion factor.  Seven surveys were conducted by the LSIB btw Oct 19 and Nov 30.  A fence operated from Oct 1 to Dec 4.  No breached were reported.  There were 706 Coho that passed through the fence prior to the following removals:  Brood:  30 M ; 30 F ; Harvest: 35 M ; 15 F.  Total escapement ( N=617) includes the fence escapement (N=596) plus the PCExp estimate (N=21) from below the fence.  Sex Ratio: M 57% ; F 43%.

EstClass: Type-7: Infill

Eight surveys were conducted by the LSIB btw Oct 19 and Dec 6.  However, Oct 19, 25 & Nov 1 surveys were removed because Chinook & Coho data were reported on each SIL and it was impossible to separate out species count info. A fence operated from Sep 25 to Dec 5.  Breaches were reported on Oct 13, Nov 3 & 4, and Nov 6,7,8, & 9.  There were 127 Coho that passed through the fence prior to the following removals:  Brood:  41 M ; 32 F ;  Total escapement ( N=51) includes the fence escapement (N=48) plus the PCExp estimate (N=3) from below the fence.  Adult Sex Ratio: M 57.9 % ; F 42.1%.

DataQualClass: 1  True Abundance with virtually no bypass
Comments: Combined estimate.  An AUC estimate (N=12) based on a 75% OE and 9 d SL was calculated for surveys conducted below the fence.  Eight surveys were conducted by the LSIB btw Oct 23 and Dec 9. A zero count end date was added. The Nov 12 survey was removed from the calculation as a result of poor environmental conditions.  A fence operated from Oct ? to Dec ?.  No breaches were reported in 2020.  There were 707 Coho that passed through the fence prior to the following removals:  Brood:  21 M ; 20 F ; Harvest: 78 M ; 40 F ; Trap Morts:  0 M;  0 F. Total escapement ( N=560) includes the fence escapement (N=548) plus the AUC estimate (N=12) from below the fence.  Sex Ratio: M 57% ; F 43%.

EstClass: Type-1B: Fence with significant Breach
DataQualClass: 3  Breach(s) reported or fence in later or removed early; no adjustment to estimate made.
Comments: Combined estimate.  An Spawners Only AUC estimate (N=44) based on a 75% OE and 9 d SL was calculated for surveys conducted below the fence.  Eight surveys were conducted by the LSIB btw Oct 14 and Dec 7. No zero counts were added. The Nov 23 survey was removed from the calculation due to the low stream visibility and reliability reported.  SEP operated the fence from Oct 1 to Nov 24.  A significant breach occurred from Nov 16 to Nov 20; The fence was down due to flooding. There were 730 Coho that passed through the fence prior to the following removals:  Brood:  16 M ; 18 F ; Harvest: 60 M ; 23 F ; Trap Morts:  0 M;  0 F. Total return to spawn ( N=657) includes the fish passed upstream of the fence (N= 613: M=318; F=295) plus the Spawners Only AUC estimate (N=44) from below the fence.  Return to Spawn Sex Ratio: M 52% ; F 48%.

EstClass: Type-4: Moderate effort (1-4 surveys), known survey method

EstClass: Type-3: High effort (5 or more surveys)
Comments: MC: True Estimate (no expansion required).  An Aerial PLExp (N=576) was calculated based on a 2.0 expansion factor.  AUCs were calculated for Maltman Channel  (N=50) and Lang Channel (N=(17/.237(index expansion)=73) based on a 75% OE and 10 d SL.  The Lang AUCs were further expanded by the channel length.

EstClass: Type-3: High effort (5 or more surveys)
Comments: MC: True Estimate (no expansion required).  A mainstem Aerial PLExp (N=144) was calculated based on a 3.0 expansion factor.  An AUC was calculated for Maltman Channel  (N=34) based on a 75% OE and 10 d SL.  A PLExp was calculated for Lang Channel using an expansion factor of 3.0.  Lang was also expanded by dividing the total length of the channel 3800 m by the survey length 900m and dividing by 0.237.

EstClass: Type-3: High effort (5 or more surveys)
Comments: AUC estimate calculated for aerial surveys of the mainstem (N=2316), Maltman (N=119) and Lang (n=65) Channels based on a 75% OE and 10 d SL.  Estimate should be based on an Aerial PLExp (N=1833) using a 3.0 expansion factor plus the AUCs from Maltman (N=119) and Lang (N=65).  The Total Return would then be 2017.

EstClass: Type-4: Moderate effort (1-4 surveys), known survey method
